President Obama has proclaimed April 19, 2016, as Education and Sharing Day, U.S.A. In his proclamation, he emphasizes the importance of providing every young person with access to a high-quality education. The President highlights his administration's efforts to expand early education and propose free community college, as well as the signing of the Every Student Succeeds Act. He also mentions the Computer Science for All initiative and the Let Girls Learn campaign, which aims to provide quality education for girls worldwide. President Obama pays tribute to Rabbi Menachem Mendel Schneerson for his dedication to extending education to all individuals, and encourages Americans to observe Education and Sharing Day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.